Tamika Cross, an OBGYN, was sitting aboard her Delta Airlines flight out of Detroit, Michigan, when another male passenger on the plane became unresponsive.

Being a doctor, Tamika’s first instinct was to rush and help the man after an attendant called overhead for asking for a physician — only to find herself being restrained by the airline crew who didn’t believe that a Black woman leaving Detroit could actually be a doctor.

You won’t even believe what happened next. Check out Tamika’s account
